'''La Yaya Dam''' is an [[embankment dam]] on the [[Guantánamo River]] near the town of La Yaya in the municipality of [[Niceto Pérez]] in [[Guantánamo Province]], [[Cuba]]. The dam was completed in 1973 for [[flood control]], irrigation of up to {{Convert|8000|ha|acre|abbr=on}}, and water supply for municipal and industrial uses. The reservoir has a storage capacity of {{Convert|160000000|m3|acre.ft|abbr=on}}, the second largest in the eastern part of the country after [[Melones Dam (Cuba)|Melones Dam]].<ref>{{cite web | url=http://www.unesco.org.uy/ci/fileadmin/phi/aqualac/Laiz_y_Flores.pdf | title=Storage Capacity Lost in Cuban Reservoirs. An Effect of Sedimentation. | publisher=UNESCO | date=September 2010 | accessdate=30 April 2014|language=Spanish}}</ref><ref>{{cite web | url=http://obras.netcons.com.cu/component/content/article/79-obras/258-entregan-certificado-acreditativo-a-las-siete-obras-fundamentales-de-la-ingenieria-de-la-provincia-de-guantanamo?directory=601 | title=Deliver a Document Certifying The Seven Fundamental Engineering Works Guantanamo Province | publisher=OBRAS | accessdate=30 April 2014 | language=Spanish}}</ref><ref>{{cite web | url=http://www.caricom.org/jsp/projects/credp/cuba_study_tour/hidroenergia_cuba.pdf | title=Situacion actual y perspectivas de las energias | accessdate=30 April 2014 |publisher=Empresa de Hidroenergia| language=Spanish}}</ref>

